attribute.name: Enable Suspicious Calculation
attribute.description: Controls the formatting of requirements, possible values are: PLAIN (the default) and HTML.

attribute.name: Enable Evaluation
attribute.description: Enables/disables the evaluation of requirements from the document.

requirementVersion.requirementText: IF any error is detected THEN the system shall switch into maintenance mode and turn on error indicator lights: All level button lights shall flash with a period of 2 Hz.
Means to prevent a livelock between floors must be implemented.
If the Cabin Door is open and the Level Position Sensor recognizes movement, although the Cabin Motor is turned off, then turn on Error Indicator Light and don't activate any motor.
requirementVersion.shortDescription: IF the cabin is overcharged THEN stop AND turn on indicator light.

requirementVersion.requirementText: All level request of opposite floors should not be considered while moving to the destination floor.
IF the cabin passes highest level THEN stop Cabin Motor AND turn error indicator light on.
Selection of multiple floors from within the car shall be possible.
IF the car is moving towards its destination floor AND still has not reached it yet AND he corresponding level call button has been pressed THEN the car should stop at each floor on the route.
requirementVersion.shortDescription: Intermediate stops to enter or leave the car

requirementVersion.requirementText: IF the cabin passes lowest level THEN stop the cabin motor AND turn error indicator light on.
IF no level call button is pressed THEN the cabin shall not move.
IF the level call button is pressed THEN move to the target floor directly.
If temperature of the Cabin Motor Tempearture Sensor recognizes a temperatur, that is higher than the maximum temperature minus 10 degree, then stop the Cabin Motor.
requirementVersion.shortDescription: IF the cabin motor is overheated THEN stop AND turn on indicator light.

requirementVersion.requirementText: If Level Position Sensor recognized the Cabin, then stop Cabin Motor, when LPS has a negative signal the first time
requirementVersion.shortDescription: IF the cabin has reached correct Position THEN stop the cabin motor.

requirementVersion.requirementText: IF the door blocked sensor returns a positive signal THEN don't close the Door.

IF any malfunction is detected between floors AND IF the controller has diagnosed it safe to operate the car THEN the car should automatically move to the nearest floor at a low speed AND stop with the doors open.
requirementVersion.shortDescription: Car control in case of malfunction

requirementVersion.requirementText: IF the cabin is recognized by any target level position sensor THEN slow down movement.
IF the cabin door is open THEN moving the cabine is not possible.
The elevator should only operate between the FloorMin and FloorMax.
The car should not stop abrupt at the destination floor. Before reaching the destination floor the traveling speed should be delayed.
If the cabin doesn't move THEN opening of the cabin door shall be possible.
IF safety relevant sensor defects are detected THEN the elevator should go into maintenance mode.
The car's traveling speed for lifting and lowering should be the same.
IF power brakdown is detected THEN the car should automatically move to the nearest floor at a low speed AND stop.
IF the cabin door is closing AND the level call button is pressed THEN the cabin door should reopen.
Doors should open and close with constant speed.

The elevator shall consist of three floors with floor level buttons on each floor. The positioning of the car shall be based on photo sensors available on each floor. The car doors shall be opened and closed using servo motors. The speed of the car shall be measured using a rotation encoder mounted at the main cabin motor.
If Level Call Button is pressed, then Level Call Light shall be on, until Cabin arrived
IF target level is reached THEN the cabin door must remain fully open for 3 seconds.
IF the cabin reaches the target level THEN open the cabin door
